{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01VK1yYCbegeC3iq21u3ww9k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DLfZgahN8atL2dBmXsMiYb","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Spiced Butternut Squash Soup.generated.21.txt","content":"Spiced Butternut Squash Soup\n\nThis warming soup recalls autumn harvests and Sunday afternoons in a farmhouse kitchen. The roasted squash becomes silky and sweet, while warming spices—cinnamon, ginger, and a touch of cayenne—create depth and complexity. Many cooks shy away from combining these flavors with soup, but the combination is unexpectedly beautiful. Serve with crusty bread and a dollop of sour cream for the perfect ending to a cool fall day.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n2 lb butternut squash, peeled and cubed\n4 tablespoons butter\n1 large onion, chopped\n3 cloves garlic, minced\n4 cups vegetable broth\n½ cup heavy cream\n1 teaspoon ground ginger\n½ teaspoon cinnamon\n¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper\nSalt and pepper to taste\nNutmeg for garnish\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Roast squash at 400°F for 20 minutes until tender\n2. Melt butter in large pot and sauté onion\n3. Add garlic and cook 1 minute\n4. Add roasted squash and broth\n5. Simmer 15 minutes\n6. Blend until smooth\n7. Stir in cream and spices\n8. Season with salt and pepper\n9. Serve hot with nutmeg\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":63686,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":63686},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e2088c48-e314-46b0-b268-2e09887642e2","uuid":"6fbdacb3-fdb6-4f61-97ac-d68fdd773a2f"}
