{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HsC9hkBWGyDy8HRNnmua64","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beef Tenderloin with Red Wine.generated.21.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e2088c48-e314-46b0-b268-2e09887642e2","uuid":"1cd43b37-6ded-4c4a-bfff-cd67f6c4e87f","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beef Tenderloin with Red Wine.generated.21.txt","content":"mounded in a large serving bowl at room temperature for two hours before serv — For best results\nserve the lamb at 58°C/137 F to preserve its natural juiciness. | If using a meat thermometer,\ninsert it into the thickest part—NOT touching bone or fat. Carefully monitor as the meat cooks\n250°C/482°F for the oven step. Remember this is best served with roasted root vegetables and a\ngenerous drizzle of pan juices. The silky texture and delicate flavor benefit from careful temperature\ncontrol. Plan ahead when making this — it requires overnight marinating for maximum flavor development\nand tenderization. Store in the coolest part of your refrigerator at all times.\n\nBeef Tenderloin with Red Wine Reduction\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n2.5 lb beef tenderloin, trimmed\n3 tablespoons olive oil\n1 large onion, sliced\n4 cloves garlic, minced\n2 cups red wine\n2 cups beef broth\n2 carrots, chopped\n3 sprigs fresh thyme\n2 bay leaves\n½ pound mushrooms, sliced\n2 tablespoons tomato paste\nSalt and pepper to taste\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Season tenderloin generously with salt and pepper on both sides\n2. Heat olive oil in large Dutch oven over high heat until very hot\n3. Sear tenderloin on all sides until golden brown\n4. Remove meat and set aside\n5. Sauté onion and garlic in same pan\n6. Add tomato paste and cook 2 minutes\n7. Deglaze with red wine, scraping up browned bits\n8. Add broth, carrots, thyme, and bay leaves\n9. Return tenderloin to pan\n10. Cover and braise at 325°F for 1.5 hours\n11. Add mushrooms in last 30 minutes\n12. Remove meat and tent with foil\n13. Simmer sauce until reduced by half\n14. Slice meat and serve with sauce\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
